  "prompt": "Nerve cell function?",
  "response": "Nerve cells, or neurons, have several key functions in the nervous system:\n\n1. Signal Transmission\n- Receive electrical and chemical signals\n- Transmit signals along their length\n- Communicate with other neurons or target cells\n\n2. Information Processing\n- Integrate incoming signals\n- Determine whether to generate an action potential\n- Conduct nerve impulses rapidly\n\n3. Neurotransmitter Release\n- Release chemical messengers at synapses\n- Enable communication between neurons\n- Facilitate signal transfer to other cells\n\n4. Communication\n- Connect different parts of the nervous system\n- Link brain, spinal cord, and peripheral tissues\n- Enable sensory and motor functions\n\n5. Signal Conversion\n- Transform external stimuli into electrical signals\n- Convert physical/chemical inputs into neural messages\n- Relay sensory information to brain\n\n6. Maintenance of Neural Networks\n- Form complex interconnected networks\n- Create synaptic connections\n- Support learning and memory processes\n\n7. Structural Components\n- Have specialized regions (dendrites, axons)\n- Maintain cellular structure\n- Support signal transmission mechanisms\n\nThese functions collectively enable neural communication, sensory perception, motor control, and cognitive processing.",
